## 3. Engine × tier matrix (3090 Ti primary)

`✓` = primary path; `◐` = secondary; `✗` = not supported / not recommended.

| Engine | T0 | T1 | T2 | T3 | T4 |
|---|---|---|---|---|---|
| ik_llama / llama.cpp | ✓ | ✓ | ◐ | ✗ | ✗ |
| SGLang | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ◐ |
| vLLM | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ | ✓ |
| TensorRT-LLM | ◐ | ◐ | ◐ | ◐ | ◐ |
| BitNet | ✓ (≤ 1B ternary) | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ |
| MLX (M1 Pro fallback only) | ✓ | ◐ | ✗ | ✗ | ✗ |

**Why this is the recommendation:**
- **T0 (drafts):** ik_llama / llama.cpp are lowest-overhead and pair naturally with speculative decoding (spec-dec needs a tiny draft model; this tier is the draft).
- **T1 (small):** SGLang's low-latency RadixAttention is excellent for the chat-loop's tight inner loop. vLLM is also fine.
- **T2 (mid):** SGLang and vLLM are roughly tied at this size on 3090 Ti. TensorRT-LLM is `◐` only because compile overhead is painful for nightly iteration; worth running once per release.
- **T3 (MoE mid):** vLLM's paged KV + chunked prefill wins for MoE on consumer GPUs. SGLang viable but slightly behind.
- **T4 (MoE large):** vLLM with AWQ + CPU offload is the only realistic local option. TensorRT-LLM `◐` because compile is rarely worth it for a single nightly.

---

## 4. Quantization strategy per tier

- **T0:** GGUF Q4_K_M. No AWQ (too coarse).
- **T1:** AWQ-INT4 default; GGUF Q5_K_M fallback for M1 Pro.
- **T2:** AWQ-INT4 default. FP8 not available on 3090 Ti (no tensor-core FP8).
- **T3 (MoE):** AWQ-INT4 on active experts; experts offloaded to CPU with `vllm cpu_offload` / SGLang equivalent.
- **T4 (MoE large):** AWQ-INT4 + CPU offload; expect batch size 1 only.
- **M1 Pro:** GGUF Q4_K_M only. No FP8, no AWQ on MLX in stable form as of mid-2026.

---

## 5. Speculative decoding strategy per tier

| Tier | Draft | Spec-dec mode |
|---|---|---|
| T0 | self (T0 model is the draft for T1+) | EAGLE-2 / P-EAGLE |
| T1 | T0 draft | EAGLE-2 / P-EAGLE; N-gram for cache-warm prompts |
| T2 | T0 or T1 draft | EAGLE-2 / dynamic spec-dec |
| T3 (MoE) | T1 draft (CPU) | EAGLE-2 only; N-gram when prefix-cache is hot |
| T4 (MoE large) | T1 draft (CPU) | EAGLE-2 only |
| Cloud (Ling) | server-side (provider controls) | unknown; measure and report |

Pheno-harness's `config/decode_acceleration_matrix.yaml` is the existing policy file. New spec-dec bindings go there.

---

## 6. vRAM budget on RTX 3090 Ti (24 GB)

Updated with live `state/hf_scrape/2026-07-03/shortlist.csv` math:

| Tier | Approx peak VRAM | Fits solo? | Fits + 1 draft? | Notes |
|---|---|---|---|---|
| T0 (1B GGUF Q4_0) | ~1.2 GB | yes | yes | trivially |
| T1 (3-4B AWQ-INT4) | 4–5 GB | yes | yes | headroom for batch 4 |
| T2 (8B AWQ-INT4, **Qwen3-8B**) | **~7 GB** | yes | yes | **workhorse fit; ~16 GB headroom** |
| T2 (12B AWQ-INT4) | ~10 GB | yes | tight | batch 1 with draft |
| T3 (30B MoE AWQ, **Qwen3-30B-A3B**) | ~21 GB | yes | marginal | all 30 B weights resident; 3 B active |
| T4 (32B AWQ-INT4, **Qwen2.5-Coder-32B**) | **~21 GB** | yes | no | **long-horizon ceiling, must unload T2** |
| T4 (70B AWQ + CPU offload) | 12–14 GB active | yes | yes | experts on CPU |
| T4 (236B MoE + heavy offload) | 18–22 GB active | marginal | marginal | long-context will spill |

**Long-context spill:** at 128K+ context, KV cache dominates. SGLang RadixAttention and vLLM paged KV both handle 128K; 262K (Ling-tier) likely needs chunked prefill + KV offload to CPU RAM.

---

## 7. Parallel agent sweep

Local 3090 Ti can sustain one T2 / T3 model at batch 1 reliably. Parallel agent count is bounded by both VRAM and effective concurrency.

| Agents | Tier achievable | Expected ttft p95 |
|---|---|---|
| 1 | T4 (Qwen2.5-Coder-32B AWQ) | < 200 ms |
| 2 | T3 (Qwen3-30B-A3B AWQ) | < 250 ms |
| 4 | T2 (Qwen3-8B AWQ) | < 300 ms |
| 8 | T1 (Qwen3-4B AWQ) | < 400 ms |
| 16 | T0 + spec-dec (Qwen3-1.7B GGUF) | < 500 ms |
| 32+ | Cloud only | (use OpenRouter) |

These are **targets**, not measurements. Sweep script is `perf/parallel_sweep.py` and emits `bench/results/perf/<date>_parallel_<n>.json` per cell.

---

## 8. M1 Pro fallback matrix (16 GB RAM)

M1 Pro is a worker / fallback only. Quantization restricted to GGUF Q4_K_M. Spec-dec on draft only.

| Tier | M1 Pro feasible? |
|---|---|
| T0 | yes |
| T1 (≤ 3B GGUF Q4_K_M) | yes, slow |
| T2 (4–12B) | no — RAM-bound, not VRAM |
| T3+ | no |

Use M1 Pro for: cache-warming, draft token generation, monitoring, and emergency fallback when 3090 Ti is busy.

---

## 9. Perf probes (what `perf/*` actually measures)

| Probe | Output | Use |
|---|---|---|
| `perf/ttft_probe.py` | TTFT p50/p95/p99 | per engine × tier × batch |
| `perf/cache_probe.py` | prefix-cache hit rate | canonicalized vs. raw prompts |
| `perf/harness_overhead.py` | harness wall time − model wall time | identify non-model latency |
| `perf/parallel_sweep.py` | N-agent fan-out | sweep N ∈ {1, 2, 4, 8, 16, 32} |
| `perf/profiler.py` | CPU/RAM/VRAM/disk/net + queue depth + leaks + deadlocks | always-on during every eval run |
| `perf/report.py` | roll-up → `bench/results/perf/<date>/` | human-readable summary |

**Crucial rule:** every probe run is paired with a non-probe reference run on the same model + same workload. The diff between probe-attached and probe-detached is the **probe overhead** itself, which is reported separately so we don't double-count.

---

## 10. Cost / price sanity (July 2026)

- `inclusionai/ling-2.6-flash` (OpenRouter): $0.01 in / $0.03 out per 1M tokens (90 % promo). Promo expiry TBD — verify on every model-binding PR.
- Local models: amortized electricity only. Pheno-harness's `eval/budget.py` should treat local as $0.
- Cost cap per eval run: see `config/budget_targets.yaml`. Default per-task ceiling: $0.50 cloud, $0.00 local.

---

## 11. Open decisions

1. **HF_TOKEN.** Sweep was unauthenticated on 2026-07-03; gated models (Mistral v0.3, Mixtral, Llama-3.1-70B, Yi-34B) are missing from `models.jsonl`. Re-run the scrape with `HF_TOKEN` set to fill T3/T4.
2. **Whether to keep TensorRT-LLM as `◐` for T4.** If a Blackwell GPU is added, promote to `✓`. Currently not worth the 30 min/calibration on 3090 Ti.
3. **Ling-tier fallback when 90 % promo expires.** Pre-negotiate a volume tier with OpenRouter or commit the T4 (Qwen2.5-Coder-32B-AWQ) as primary local fallback.
4. **DeepSeek-V3 685 B at home.** Not in scope on 64 GB DDR4; would need a 128 GB RAM upgrade. Skipped for this round.
5. **Qwen3-30B-A3B-FP8 vs Qwen3-30B-A3B-AWQ.** FP8 doesn't fit 24 GB (FP8 weights for 30 B ≈ 30 GB, no headroom). AWQ wins.

---

## 12. First matrix sweep (the actual waypoint)

Run order for the first batch (revised with live 2026-07-03 shortlist):

1. **T0 sweep:** `Qwen3-1.7B` + `Qwen2.5-0.5B` + `Llama-3.2-1B` + `Gemma-3-1B` × ik_llama + SGLang + vLLM. Pick the winner as the universal draft.
2. **T1 sweep:** `Qwen3-4B-Instruct-2507` + `Llama-3.2-3B` + `Phi-3.5-mini` + `StarCoder2-3B` + `Qwen2.5-Coder-1.5B` × SGLang + vLLM + llama.cpp. Pick best per-task-type.
3. **T2 sweep:** `Qwen3-8B` (workhorse) + `Llama-3.1-8B` + `Qwen2.5-Coder-7B` + `Qwen3-Coder-30B-A3B-AWQ` (MoE) × SGLang + vLLM (AWQ). Pick best per-task-type.
4. **T3 sweep (after HF_TOKEN):** `Mixtral-8x7B-AWQ` + `OLMoE-1B-7B` + `Phi-tiny-MoE` × vLLM (AWQ).
5. **T4 sweep:** `Qwen2.5-Coder-32B-AWQ` (workhorse heavy) + `Qwen3-32B-AWQ` + `CodeLlama-34B-AWQ` × vLLM (AWQ).
6. **T5 parity check:** `ling-2.6-flash` on OpenRouter vs. local T3 (Qwen3-30B-A3B-AWQ) for the same 16-task subset.
7. **M1 fallback:** `Qwen3-1.7B` + `Llama-3.2-1B` + `Qwen3-4B` (GGUF Q4_0) on llama.cpp / MLX.